The Democratic Alliance has welcomed former president Jacob Zuma's arrest, but says, there are still loose ends that need to tied up. The party says more still needs to be done to reclaim the country, from what it calls 'predatory politicians'. eNCA's Clement Manyathela speaks to party leader John Steenhuisen. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma's arrest is a victory for the rule of law, but he shouldn't be alone in prison. That's the word from DA leader, John Steenhuisen. WATCH: South Africans react to Zuma's arrest He says Zuma didn't act alone in state capture, and all of the individuals implicated should also be imprisoned. Steenhuisen says it's encouraging that the wheels of justice are turning but it's just the tip of the iceberg.